      <section>
        <h2>üß† Prompt Engineering: CRIT Framework</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>C ‚Äî Context:</strong> Give background, the situation, the class, the topic.</li>
          <li><strong>R ‚Äî Role:</strong> Tell the AI how to behave (e.g., ‚Äúact as my research assistant‚Äù).</li>
          <li><strong>I ‚Äî Interview:</strong> What follow-up questions should it ask you?</li>
          <li><strong>T ‚Äî Task:</strong> What output do you actually want?</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- Ethical AI -->
      <section>
        <h2>‚öñÔ∏è Ethical + Safe AI Use (From the Workshop)</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Always double-check facts ‚Äî AI can hallucinate confidently.</li>
          <li>Do NOT paste personal names, private info, or sensitive data.</li>
          <li>AI has no concept of truth ‚Äî verify everything.</li>
          <li>You are the manager. Final work = your responsibility.</li>
          <li>Think in ‚ÄúGreen / Yellow / Red‚Äù tasks depending on risk.</li>
          <li>AI reflects biases in its training data ‚Äî stay critical.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

